│ THOUGHT: The crash arises when SLPVectorizer's GenerateLoadsSubkey calls getUnderlyingObject on a possibly problematic pointer operand, leading to a segfault inside        │
│ Value::getType. A simple and safe fix is to avoid getUnderlyingObject in this context and use the load's pointer operand directly for grouping and hashing. I will update   │
