│ THOUGHT: The crash persists because SLPVectorizer's GenerateLoadsSubkey still calls getUnderlyingObject on load pointer operands that can be problematic. A robust fix is   │
│ to stop calling getUnderlyingObject there and group loads directly by their pointer operands. I will update all occurrences where Ptr is computed via getUnderlyingObject   │
│ to use LI->getPointerOperand() instead, rebuild, and verify the reproducer no longer crashes, then submit the patch.                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                             │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ sed -i 's/Value *Ptr = getUnderlyingObject(LI->getPointerOperand());/Value *Ptr = LI->getPointerOperand();/g;s/auto \*Ptr =                                                 │
│ getUnderlyingObject(LI->getPointerOperand());/auto *Ptr = LI->getPointerOperand();/g' /llvm-autofix-deps/llvm/llvm/llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp && ninja │
