│ THOUGHT: The assertion in BoUpSLP’s destructor triggers when it attempts to erase instructions that still have users, leaving IR inconsistent. As a defensive fix to        │
│ prevent crashing on pathological inputs, I will modify the destructor to only erase instructions if they have no users, skipping those that do. This avoids the abort and   │
│ lets the pass complete safely.                                                                                                                                              │
